coregtk
=======

The CoreGTK website can be found at: http://www.coregtk.org/

CoreGTK is an Objective-C language binding for the GTK+ widget toolkit. CoreGTK is free software, licensed under the GNU LGPL.

Building & Installing CoreGTK:
---------------------------

	CoreGTK is built on top of the GNUstep or Foundation libraries. You will need a compatible Objective-C compiler, runtime and foundation library. On Debian/Ubuntu, this can be done using:
	apt-get install gcc gnustep-core-devel

    You will also need to install the gtk-2 development headers. On Debian/Ubuntu, this can be done using:
    apt-get install libgtk2.0-dev

    The build will vary depending on platform.
    
    On Linux run:
    	make linux
    	
    On Mac OSX run:
    	make mac

	On Windows run:
		make windows

Developers:
-----------

    For developers wishing to "get started" with CoreGTK, they are encouraged
    to read the developers pages at:

        http://www.coregtk.org
